==Irish==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[ˈeg&#690;ə]}}
===Prepositional pronoun===
[[Third person]] [[singular]] [[masculine]] [[pronoun]] fused with preposition [[ag]] '[[at]]'
#[[at]] [[him]]

===Usage===
Used as the predicate of the verb [[bí]] 'to [[be]]' to indicate possession:
:''Tá leabhar aige'' &mdash; He has a book
==Scottish Gaelic==
'''aige'''
===Prepositional pronoun===
# Amalgamation of ''aig'', [[at]], and ''e'', [[he]], to form "at [[him]]" or "at [[it]]" in regards to masculine nouns.
===Usage===
Used as the predicate of the verb ''[[a bhith]]'', to [[be]], to indicate possession (i.e. to say that X is at Y is to say that Y has X.):
:''Chan eil fhios aige'' &mdash; Knowledge is not at him (He doesn't know.).